 Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":25,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William Stebbing was born in 1430, in Devon, England, his father, Walter Stebbing I, was 32 and his mother, Christian Bodrugan, was 5. He had at least 2 sons with Mabell Holway Small. He died in 1482, in Devon, England, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1430–1490":"1430–1490","1430–1455":"1430–1455","1430–1482":"1430–1482","1430–1459":"1430–1459","1460–1490":"1460–1490","1475–1555":"1475–1555","1398–1462":"1398–1462","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","1555":"1555","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1398":"1398","1430":"1430","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","1471":"1471","1482":"1482","1490":"1490","Kettleburgh, Suffolk, England":"Kettleburgh, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Townstall, Devon, England":"Townstall, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Fenne, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1430–1490":"1430–1490","1430–1455":"1430–1455","1430–1482":"1430–1482","1430–1459":"1430–1459","1460–1490":"1460–1490","1475–1555":"1475–1555","1398–1462":"1398–1462","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","1555":"1555","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1398":"1398","1430":"1430","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","1471":"1471","1482":"1482","1490":"1490","Kettleburgh, Suffolk, England"